					<item>
				<guid>http://bvs.wikidot.com/forum/t-54161#post-147398</guid>
				<title>Re: Apr. 17: Advanced Upgrade Voting</title>
				<link>http://bvs.wikidot.com/forum/t-54161/apr-17:advanced-upgrade-voting#post-147398</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 17 Apr 2008 16:14:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>BvS-Uzuki</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>78144</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Re: Epic Monument.</p> <p>Short Answer: I don't think it's possible.</p> <p>Long Answer: The hard part about going Epic is the 6 advanced resources you need, 3 ice and 3 fire. At a minimum that means you need to be able to accomplish 3 invasions without having anything you've taken be taken back from you. In practice, it often takes more than this.</p> <p>Through some hoop jumping, we can get 3 attacks in one day, but the bare minimum of 3 attacks only works completely well if you have 3 of your local resource already, which is only really possible if you go peacetime to stack em up. Even then, we need to use <a class="newpage" href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/items:rotating-timespheres">Rotating Timespheres</a>, and we'd need to do some Kage manipulation to pull it off (or do some really risky stuff right at day roll).</p> <p>All of this is made easier by killing the <a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/monster:storm-riders">Storm Riders</a> to get <a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:trophaeum-tower">Trophaeum Tower</a>. (Combined, of course, with Rotating Timespheres). This is part of the reason why I'm backing Hard Corpsâ€¦to make it easier to kill Storm Riders when we get them, so we can get Trophaeum Tower, so we can get an Epic Monument.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
