				<wikidot:authorName>BvS-Uzuki</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>78144</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Upgrades that involve advanced resources take priority over ones that do not.</p> <h3><span>Natural Research Facility Upgrades</span></h3> <ul> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:quiet-glade">Quiet Glade</a> - 1 - OmnifoxGE</li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:tall-walls">Tall Walls</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:sabotage-facility">Sabotage Facility</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:bodyguard-squad">Bodyguard Squad</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:village-memorial">Village Memorial</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:medical-ninja-facility">Medical Ninja Facility</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:elemental-harmony">Elemental Harmony</a> - 3 - Ainn, GogoluG, Lear</li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:ninja-cooking-school">Ninja Cooking School</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:chakra-training-center">Chakra Training Center</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:jutsu-enhancement-tower">Jutsu Enhancement Tower</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:ancient-teachings">Ancient Teachings</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:sneaky-tricks">Sneaky Tricks</a> - 1 - Darkshard</li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:ninja-ambassadors">Ninja Ambassadors</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:spartan-battleground">Spartan Battleground</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:hard-corps">Hard Corps</a> - 8 - Ananvil, ApocGE, Arkantos, Bayard, Jupiah, naito, schon, Uzuki</li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:eternal-mirrors">Eternal Mirrors</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:infinite-awareness">Infinite Awareness</a></li> <li><a href="http://bvs.wikidot.com/upgrade:epic-monument">Epic Monument</a></li> </ul> <p>Voting will continue until we have the resources to purchase whatever is currently in the lead. In the event of upgrades that require a certain number of people, we may go to the #2 option if we don't have the appropriate number of people and it doesn't look like we will any time soon.</p> <p>Please vote in the following format:</p> <blockquote> <p>Vote: &lt;Character Name&gt; - &lt;Upgrade Preference&gt;</p> </blockquote> 
